<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Highly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Highly,</orth> 1) high, far above the ground: <cit><quote>mountainous error be too h. heaped,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 127</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) in an elevated place, style, or manner: <cit><quote>h. fed and lowly taught,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 2, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>ditties h. penned,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 209</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>wherein thyself shalt h. be employed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.180" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 180</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) in a great degree, very much: <emph>h. praised,</emph> Ven. Ded. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.180" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 180</bibl> <cit><quote>things that women h. hold in hate,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 2, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. beloved,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her wit values itself so h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 53</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.245" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 245</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.245" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 245</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 5, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.29" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 6, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 33</bibl>.
